Title: The Clampetts Strike Oil
Synopsis: A rural Ozark family relocates to Beverly Hills after oil is discovered on their property worth $25 million. After finding oil on the land, the family is surprised when Mr. Brewster (Frank Wilcox) of the OK Oil Company offers to buy it. After much coaxing by Cousin Pearl (Bea Benaderet), Jed (Buddy Ebsen) sells the swamp and moves the family to a mansion in Beverly Hills. Upon their arrival, they are arrested because of a case of mistaken identity but are later returned to the mansion safely.
Author: Paul Henning
Quote: "You know Granny, that's one of them air fields, sets up in the air."

Title: Getting Settled
Synopsis: The rough-hewn Clampetts are mistaken for servants as they try to adapt to their new environment.
Author: Paul Henning

Title: Meanwhile, Back at the Cabin
Synopsis: Jane Hathaway finds that making the Clampetts more sophisticated will be harder than expected, while Pearl Bodine tries to get the attention of Mr. Brewster.
Author: Paul Henning
Supplemental: The series opener shows just how appealing money can be, especially to the Clampetts. Selling thier oil rich swamp for millions leads them to the strange new place of Beverly Hills.

Title: The Clampetts Meet Mrs. Drysdale
Synopsis: Mr. Drysdale tries furiously to make the Clampetts more acceptable to his socially-conscious wife.
Author: Paul Henning

Title: Jed Buys Stock
Synopsis: Upon Mr. Drysdale's advice to buy good stock, Jed purchases cows, pigs, and chickens to raise.
Author: Paul Henning

Title: Trick or Treat
Synopsis: The homesick Clampetts decide to go door-to-door meeting their Beverly Hills neighbors, not knowing it is Halloween.
Author: Paul Henning

Title: The Servants
Synopsis: Yet another Drysdale attempt to "reform" the Clampetts goes awry when he tries to loan his servants to the hard-working family.
Author: Paul Henning

Title: Jethro Goes to School
Synopsis: The headmistress (Eleanor Audley) of an exclusive private school for boys is astonished to find the teenaged Jethro enrolled in her fifth grade.
Author: Paul Henning

Title: Jed Gets the Misery
Synopsis: Jed pretends to be sick so that granny can get to doctoring and feel more at home. Mr Drysdale and his physician get pulled into the ploy and Granny's mountain medicine is put to the test by a city doctor.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle
Quote: "I opened the window, but, but I didn't breathe. Oh, I swear it! I held my breath, didn't I Mr. Clampett?"

Title: Hair-Raising Holiday
Synopsis: Jed pretends to be sick so that granny can get to doctoring and feel more at home. Mr Drysdale and his physician get pulled into the ploy and Granny's mountain medicine is put to the test by a city doctor.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle
Supplemental: Jed cheers up Grannie by pretending to be sick so she can doctor him. Soon Drysdale and his doctor, Clyburn, are subject to her methods as well.

Title: Elly Starts to School
Synopsis: Miss Hathaway's worry that Elly May won't fit in at a private school proves to be premature.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: The Clampett Look
Synopsis: The Clampetts unwittingly become the pioneers of a fashion style that everybody who's everybody is wearing.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: Jethro's First Love
Synopsis: Jethro develops feelings for an exotic dancer named Chickadee (Barbara Nichols), and brings her home to meet the folks.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: Chickadee Returns
Synopsis: As marriage seemingly draws nearer, Jethro discovers a deal-breaking secret about Chickadee: she can't cook.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: The Clampetts Are Overdrawn
Synopsis: An unemployed actor named J.D. Clampett benefits from a paperwork mixup at the bank, becoming $36 million richer.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: The Clampetts Go Hollywood
Synopsis: Newly-discovered "cousin" Jake Clampett decides that the hillbillies should act more like Hollywood movie stars (Jake purchases a brand new 1964 Imperial convertible to improve Jed's image, but the car is never seen again – the Clampett family truck is Jed's choice of vehicle).
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: Jed Becomes A Movie Mogul
Synopsis: Jed purchases a movie studio, leading him to meet many stars and Elly May to try her hand on the silver screen.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle
Quote: "Now Miss Jane, ain't no call to go mean mouthin' me."

Title: Clampett City
Synopsis: The Western set on the backlot of their movie studio provides the Clampetts with a taste of home.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: Clampett City General Store
Synopsis: As the Clampetts open the "general store" on their Western set to customers, Jethro, Elly May, and Granny are cast in a picture about Nero and Cleopatra.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle
Supplemental: Chaplin tries to impress Jed and his clan by showing him a new picture and putting Elly in movies. She doesn’t do well and scares Sir Trevor out.

Title: Hedda Hopper's Hollywood
Synopsis: Famed Hollywood gossip columnist Hedda Hopper urges Jed not to allow the historic movie studio to be torn down, but changes her mind when she sees the film the Clampetts have made there.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: Doctor Jed Clampett
Synopsis: Jed receives an honorary doctorate, but the family thinks he now has the power to heal.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: Jed the Heartbreaker
Synopsis: Mrs. Drysdale decides to use her womanly charms on Jed, in an effort to scare the Clampetts back to the hills.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle
Supplemental: Drysdale has hopes that Jed will buy a yacht and join the yacht club with him. The Clampetts are all ready to go, except for Granny who has been listening to Jethro and is now afraid of drowning and sharks.

Title: Back to Marineland
Synopsis: After being turned down in his aspiration to be a "double naught spy", Jethro decides to join the Marines by getting a job at Marineland.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: Teenage Idol
Synopsis: Teen singing sensation Johnny Poke, a friend from back in the hills, visits the Clampetts. Alan Reed guest stars.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: Admiral Jed Clampett
Synopsis: Granny's fear of sharks makes her reluctant to go yachting with the rest of the family. (This is the first episode filmed and aired in color).
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle
Quote: "Tell her that even if the shark does get her, it's quicker than drownin'."-

Title: That Old Black Magic
Synopsis: Granny thinks her study of astrology has turned Mrs. Drysdale into a bird.
Author: Ronny Pearlman

Title: The Sheik
Synopsis: Jethro appreciates Arabic culture when Jed's new oil partner, a sheikh, arrives with his harem.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: The Private Eye
Synopsis: Jethro's attempt to become a "double naught spy" unwittingly leads him to foil a bank robbery.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: Possum Day
Synopsis: Mr. Drysdale tries to get the city of Beverly Hills to celebrate Possum Day in order to keep the Clampetts from returning home.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle
Supplemental: Granny and Jethro return to Elly and Jed, who has been suffering his daughter’s cooking for a while, from visiting Pearl back home. Granny returns with presents and a new device – a telephone.

Title: The Possum Day Parade
Synopsis: Granny campaigns dirty against Mrs. Drysdale for the title of Possum Queen.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: The Clampetts Play the Rams
Synopsis: Jethro's date, Mr. Drysdale's maid, is more interested in watching his color television than in him.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: The Courtship of Elly
Synopsis: Granny's love potion for Elly May affects Miss Jane's boyfriend.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle

Title: The Party Line
Synopsis: Granny and Jethro return from visiting the hills with an old-fashioned telephone to communicate with home.
Author: Paul Henning & Mark Tuttle
Quote: "Well, Granny left enough vittles for a couple of weeks. But since that run out, its been mostly roots and berries. And they is a squirrel I'm right beholdin' to for nuts."

Title: The Soup Contest
Synopsis: In an attempt to attract suitors for Elly May, Granny enters some of her own soup in a contest under the girl's name.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson

Title: Jethro Takes Love Lessons
Synopsis: Despite getting advice from an expert, Jethro remains unlucky at romance.
Author: Mark Tuttle & Ronny Pearlman

Title: The Badger Game
Synopsis: A young girl posing as an acquaintance from back home tries to blackmail Jed with some compromising photographs.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson

Title: The Badgers Return
Synopsis: A pair of con artists use the Clampetts' unwitting assistance to try to blackmail Mr. Drysdale.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson

Title: The Gorilla
Synopsis: After the Clampetts request a gorilla to help out with housework, Mr. Drysdale hires a man in a costume to change their minds.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson

Title: Come Back, Little Herbie
Synopsis: The man in the gorilla costume takes advantage of the Clampett's lifestyle when he's supposed to be working.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson
Supplemental: Jethro even makes Granny wear an oaf costume, since she doesn't have Clampett blood. Drysdale and Jane visit, and Jane tells the Clampetts that what Jethro is telling them is wrong. But after Drysdale paints a picture for Jane, the two convince the Clampetts to go, even providing an oaf for Jethro, Miss Jane. After Jethro finally makes Granny "royalty," the clan, dressed in normal clothes, goes to get their passports.

Title: Jed in Politics
Synopsis: The government tells Granny to stop making her lye soap because it is causing smog, so Jed decides to run for the office of Smog Commissioner.
Author: Mark Tuttle & Ronny Pearlman

Title: Jed Inherits A Castle
Synopsis: Jethro informs Jed that he has acquired a castle in England, after hearing the word from Drysdale. He gets costumes from Tudor times, thinking that Queen Elizabeth I is still ruling.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson
Quote: "And there is no debtors prison. No torture for those overdrawn at the bank."

Title: The Clampetts In London
Synopsis: The Clampetts are on the plane to England, with "Sir Jethro" as their leader. But with this comes a detour. The Clampetts get off the aeroplane in San Francisco, after Jethro presumes it is England.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson

Title: Mr Universe Muscles In
Synopsis: Elly is preparing for her date with Troy Apollo, which was set up by John Cushing from the Merchant's Bank.
Author: Mark Tuttle & Deborah Haber

Title: Greetings From The President
Synopsis: Just as the Clampetts are getting ready to go home to the hills, Jethro gets a draft notification from the President of the US.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson

Title: The Army Game
Synopsis: An Army psychologist thinks Jethro is pretending to be crazy to avoid military service.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson

Title: A Plot for Granny
Synopsis: Jed's plan to buy Granny some land out in the country backfires when he mistakenly purchases a cemetery plot.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson
Supplemental: After learning it was ships that have been sold, the Clampetts decide the Queen needs help, and they decide to take out their money and give it to the Her Majesty.

Title: The Social Climbers
Synopsis: Jed is aggressively courted by a young socialite widow from back in the hills.
Author: Mark Tuttle & Deborah Haber

Title: Jethro's Military Career
Synopsis: Jed thinks Granny has had too much moonshine when she mistakes Jethro in a frogman suit for a sea monster.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson

Title: The Reserve Program
Synopsis: Jethro mistakes a movie set as being the planning stages of a second Civil War, and runs home to warn Granny.
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson

Title: The South Rides Again
Synopsis: Granny, Elly May, and Jethro take the fight to the enemy and rout the "Yankee invaders".
Author: Paul Henning & Buddy Atkinson

Title: A Bundle for Britain
Synopsis: The Clampetts feel that their eighty million dollars in the bank is a burden to Mr. Drysdale, so they decide to relieve him by giving it to the Queen of the United Kingdom.
Author: Gene Thompson
Quote: "Did you ever try hitchhiking from the airport, wearing a suit of armor and totin' a buzzard?"

Title: Something For the Queen
Synopsis: After flying to England and their castle, Granny decides the clan should reignite a year-old feud with the neighboring castle.
Author: Buddy Atkinson & Gene Thompson

Title: War of the Roses
Synopsis: Jethro determines that a joust is the best way to end the dispute between the neighboring castles, though everyone else thinks that they're just talking about the War of the Roses.
Author: Buddy Atkinson & Gene Thompson

Title: Coming Through the Rye
Synopsis: The Clampetts see a man in a kilt and believe Jethro has confused him for a young lady.
Author: Buddy Atkinson & Gene Thompson
Supplemental: Granny is afraid of a mountain lion she sees in her root cellar, and Elly May reveals it is hers. But after reading the paper and seeing that Elverna Bradshaw’s daughter is getting married, Granny tells Jed they need to go home and return to the Hills to get Elly married first.

Title: Ghost of Clampett Castle
Synopsis: Mr. Drysdale dresses like a ghost, hoping to scare the Clampetts into returning to Beverly Hills.
Author: Buddy Atkinson

Title: Granny Goes to Hooterville
Synopsis: Granny goes back to the hills to take care of a newborn baby
Author: Buddy Atkinson & Dick Wesson

Title: Back to the Hills
Synopsis: Granny wants to return to the hills to find Elly May a husband.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson
Quote: "I'll get you a bowl Miss Jane. I'm glad to see somebody else getting' some cereal. Jed has been stuffin' hisself all mornin'."

Title: The Hills of Home
Synopsis: The Clampetts travel to the hills and meet up with nemesis Elverna Bradshaw, who makes a bet with Granny that her daughter will be married before Elly May.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: Silver Dollar City Fair
Synopsis: Granny goes to great lengths to get Elly a husband.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: Jane Finds Elly a Man
Synopsis: Miss Jane discovers a prospective husband for Elly May while birdwatching.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: Wedding Plans
Synopsis: Granny plans Elly May's wedding with her "fiance", and misunderstands his proposition.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: Jed Buys Central Park
Synopsis: A grimy con man (Phil Silvers) tricks the Clampetts into buying Central Park.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: The Clampetts in New York
Synopsis: The family sees all the sights of New York, and attempts to set up a cabin in Central Park.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: Manhattan Hillbillies
Synopsis: Granny has fun with a black Irish police officer (Sammy Davis, Jr.) while they are visiting in New York.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: The Clampetts in Washington
Synopsis: The con artists follow the Clampetts to Washington, and sell them the White House.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson
Quote: "I'll likely be in the East Room or some place sittin' on his Cabinet."
Supplemental: The Clampetts head to Washington D.C to give their money to the President, and Honest John and Flo follow.

Title: Jed Buys the Capitol
Synopsis: Jed gets swindled into buying the Capitol Building and the Clampetts are taken to a psych ward for evaluation.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: Mark Templeton Arrives
Synopsis: Mark Templeton, a Navy frogman, arrives to court Elly May, but Granny misunderstands his profession and thinks he is half-human, half-frog.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: Don't Marry a Frogman
Synopsis: Granny puts her medical knowledge to work trying to figure out a cure for being half-frog.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: Doctor, Cure My Frog
Synopsis: Granny is alarmed that Elly May and Jethro want to be frogmen like Mark.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: Do You Elly Take This Frog?
Synopsis: Granny is desperate to keep Elly May from going into the water with Mark, believing she too will turn into a frog.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: The Frog Family
Synopsis: To add to Granny's distress, Jed decides he too would like to be a frogman.
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: Farm in the Ocean
Synopsis: Mr. Drysdale and Granny team up to run the frogman away from Elly May
Author: Paul Henning & Dick Wesson

Title: A Rose for Lotta
Synopsis: Silver barons use an actress called Lotta Crabtree in a plot to hold Joe Cartwright hostage in exchange for timber wood.
Author: David Dortort
Quote: "Hop Sing, you know you can't do that. Why if you left here, I'd waste away to a shadow. You know that."

Title: The Sun Mountain Herd
Synopsis: A pair of greedy opportunists kiil antelope on Indian grounds and sell them for a large profit.
Author: David Dortort and Gene L. Coon

Title: The Newcomers
Synopsis: Hoss falls for the fiancee of a treacherous prospector who suspects the Cartwrights of hiding gold.
Author: Thomas Thompson

Title: The Paiute War
Synopsis: A sinister trader starts a war with the Paiutes when he frames Adam for the assault of two Indian women.
Author: Gene L. Coon
Supplemental: In the series opener, Ben refuses to sell the Ponderosa's timber to Alpheus Troy and his business cartel that wanting it for mine building.

Title: Enter Mark Twain
Synopsis: As reporter Samuel Clemens, Mark Twain leads a fight against a corrupt judge.
Author: Harold Shumate

Title: The Julia Bulette Story
Synopsis: Joe falls for gold digger Julia Bulette.
Author: Al C. Ward

Title: The Saga of Annie O'Toole
Synopsis: Annie O'Toole uses a filed claim to protect her gold mine.
Author: Thomas Thompson

Title: The Philip Diedesheimer Story
Synopsis: Pied Pioer Philip Diedesheimer fails to get paid for saving the salt mines of Virginia City from a cave-in.
Author: Thomas Thompson

Title: The Secret
Synopsis: Joe is the victim of an elaborate frame-up, accused of murdering a pregnant girl.
Author: John Hawkins

Title: The Dream Riders
Synopsis: To finance his dream of constructing an airship capable of crossing the Atlantic, Ben's old friend plans to rob the Virginia City bank while diverting the citizens' attention with a hot air balloon.
Author: James Van Wagoner, Jack McClain

Title: Elizabeth My Love
Synopsis: At the bedside of a seriously ill Adam, Ben thinks back to his days as a first mate in the merchant marines and his marriage to Adam's mother, Elizabeth Stoddard.
Author: Anthony Lawrence

Title: Sam Hill
Synopsis: Blacksmith Sam Hill fights to keep the land on which his mother is buried, after his drunken father signs the deed over to Colonel Tyson and his private army.
Author: David Dortort

Title: The Last Viking
Synopsis: Hoss meets his Uncle Gunnar for the first time, unaware that he commands a band of raiding comancheros.
Author: Anthony Lawrence

Title: The Trail Gang
Synopsis: On a cattle drive back to Nevada from Texas, Ben hires a young man who is both an outlaw and the son of the sheriff whose town the Ponderosa cowhands are entering.
Author: Carey Wilber

Title: The Savage
Synopsis: Adam's life is saved by a woman known to the Indians as White Buffalo Woman, but who is actually the daughter of Norwegian immigrants.
Author: Joseph Stone, Paul King

Title: Silent Thunder
Synopsis: Little Joe becomes friendly with a deaf-mute named Ann Croft and tries to teach her sign language.
Author: John Furia

Title: The Ape
Synopsis: The Ape Hoss becomes friends with dull-witted Arnie Gurnie, who is a brute of a man with the mentality of a child. His temper scares everybody, including the Cartwrights.
Author: Gene L. Coon

Title: The Blood Line
Synopsis: Ben feels responsible for the son of a man he was forced to kill, but the young man is determined to get even. A professional gunman offers to do the job for him.
Author: William Raynor, Myles Wilder

Title: Andy's Rival
Synopsis: Opie has his first crush, who ignores him. Crestfallen he turns to Andy and Barney for advice. Barney steps in and tries to give him his advice about women.
Author: Peter Baldwin
Quote: "Of course Helen is lucky to have you too."

Title: Malcolm at the Crossroads
Synopsis: Malcolm Merriweather replaces Ernest T. Bass as school crossing guard, starting a conflict.
Author: Gary Nelson

Title: Aunt Bee, the Swinger
Synopsis: Aunt Bee and her new beau attempt to recapture their youth.
Author: Larry Dobkin
Supplemental: Andy gets jealous when a big-city teacher arrives to work with Helen and ends up spending several evenings with her.

Title: The Bazaar
Synopsis: Andy's new deputy, Warren Ferguson, arrests Aunt Bee and her friends for gambling at the church bazaar.
Author: Sheldon Leonard

Title: A Warning from Warren
Synopsis: Warren believes a picnic will not go so well for Andy and Helen.
Author: Alan Rafkin

Title: Off to Hollywood
Synopsis: The Taylors decide to take a trip to Hollywood after Andy is given a check from a studio that wants to make his life into a movie.
Author: Alan Rafkin

Title: Taylors in Hollywood
Synopsis: The Taylors visit the studio where the movie based on Andy's life, Sheriff Without a Gun, is being shot.
Author: Alan Rafkin

Title: The Hollywood Party
Synopsis: Andy poses with a Hollywood starlet, jeopardizing his relationship with Helen.
Author: Alan Rafkin

Title: Aunt Bee on TV
Synopsis: Aunt Bee wins a lot of new appliances on a TV quiz show, but she loses her friends as a result.
Author: Alan Rafkin

Title: The Cannon
Synopsis: Through sheer luck, Warren catches a pair of thieves with his supposed "knowledge" of cannons.
Author: Alan Rafkin

Title: The Sheriff of Smoke Tree
Synopsis: No one in the town of Smoke Tree will take the job of Sheriff; they are too terrified to fight the Lem Carter gang. It is up to The Lone Ranger to step in and free the town from the gangâs iron fist.
Author: Fran Striker
Supplemental: The Lone Ranger and Tonto go into action when a little mining camp proves too small, and a gang of gunfighters too tough, to permit a full time sheriff.

Title: The Counterfeit Mask
Synopsis: A gunman the Lone Ranger helped convict and sent to prison takes revenge by posing in an identical Lone Ranger uniform to rob, pillage and murder.
Author: Fran Striker

Title: No Handicap
Synopsis: The Lone Ranger and Tonto clash with a band of marauders that are terrorizing a wide area of the southwest
Author: Fran Striker

Title: The Cross of Santo Domingo
Synopsis: The Lone Ranger and Tonto, riding through the desert, encounter outlaws who have stolen the golden, jeweled Cross of Santo Domingo.
Author: Fran Striker

Title: White Hawk's Decision
Synopsis: The Lone Ranger and Tonto help an elderly Indian chief determine the future of his impoverished tribe through the choice of which son will succeed him.
Author: Fran Striker

Title: The Return of Don Pedro O'Sullivan
Synopsis: The Lone Ranger impersonates two men in his efforts to help a Mexican patriot cross the border into Mexico to battle a dictator.
Author: Fran Striker

Title: Calling Doctor Baxter
Synopsis: Bob tries to find a husband for his widowed sister, Margaret.
Author: PHenning

Title: Collins The Crooner
Synopsis: A newspaper columnist reports that Bob is to record an album.
Author: PHenning, DWeson

Title: The Hot Dog Stand
Synopsis: David, Wally, and Chuck take over management of the campus hot dog stand.
Author: Ozzie, Don Nelson
Quote: "They won't let you eat in class"-Ozzie

Title: David and the Mermaid
Synopsis: David is in an ocean of trouble with June when he goes missing with a beautiful mermaid.
Author: Ozzie, Don Nelson
Supplemental: Managing the Hot dog stand seemed like a great idea, until the boys run into some unexpected trouble.

Title: Tonsils
Synopsis: Riley visits the company doctor after swallowing a small fish bone. The doctor finds he's suffering from tonsillitis and needs an operation immediately.
Author: Merwin Gerard
Quote: "It began here in the Allied bar and grille"-narrator

Title: Babs and Simon Step Out
Synopsis: Riley's insistence that Babs has nothing to do with Simon comes between him and Babs. He forbids her to see him, then when she sneaks around behind his back, he chases Simon off. Both his wife and daughter are very upset with him.
Author: Collier Young/Larry Marcus

Title: Stampede at Tent City
Synopsis: Bat encounters a group of wranglers who are stealing horses. A old flame of Bat's asks him to rescue her current beau, accused of murder and shackled to a tree by a lynch mob led by the slain man's brother who leads the wranglers.
Author: Frank Pitman
Quote: "Listen, I'm going to stay in your town or a while."-Bat

Title: The Fighter
Synopsis: Bat wins the contract of a young fighter from his unscrupulous manager, then trains him for one honest fight, betting all his poker winnings on it. The boxer's former manager doesn't want a fair fight and plans to ensure the boxer loses.
Author: Frank Pitman
Supplemental: On May 20, 1886 Bat arrives in Silverton, Colorado where he finds a fight in progress but when the manager of the fight ties the right arm of the younger fighter down, Bat soon intervenes as the young man takes a beating.

Title: Goldie Crosses the Tracks
Synopsis: Goldie, a showgirl turned manicurist, becomes the guardian of three teenagers when she is named executrix of a millionaire's estate.
Author: Stanley Roberts
Quote: "No, not you I was Talking to Nicky"-Dad
Supplemental: A talkative manicurist inherits a legacy and the custody of three children from a rich Wall Street broker customer.

Title: Art for Goldie's Sake
Synopsis: Pat decides to move to Greenwich Village and to study art with a bunch of beatniks in spite of Goldie's objections.
Author: Stanley Roberts
Quote: "I can lower myself with my shoelaces"-Goldie

Title: High Fever
Synopsis: Vickie insists that Gus receive medical treatment when he comes down with a low-grade temperature, but the only doctor she is able to locate is a wisecracking obstetrician.
Author: George Tibbles, Bill Kelsay
Supplemental: Big men are little boys, and little boys are husbands

Title: The Tree in the Driveway
Synopsis: Vickie gets the neighbors to sign a petition to stop the city from removing a tree from the parkway.
Author: George Tibbles, Bill Kelsay
Quote: "Nobody stays more than 20 minutes past coffe cake"-Vickie
